		<Quote>'My immortality is drenched in red.'</Quote>
		<NPCRecruitmentText>I'm a refined noble who tends to have animalistic cravings from time to time. That's one tasty looking jugular I might add... Yes I can float around for a while but it will cost you %d gildar. My tailor has outrageous prices.</NPCRecruitmentText>
		<Backstory>Summer was in full swing, with its load of buzzing flies and hots tempers. Earl Von Brakov became increasingly restless while supervising the change of guard and listening to the accountant's numbers for the season's harvest. Each and every day with no end in sight. When an Undead raiding party was sighted on the outskirts of the Blackveil Forest and reported to be moving straight for the castle, the Earl felt strangely elated. Finally, something exciting was about to happen. With little preparation, with his saddle belt barely secured, he rushed out with forty mounted soldiers to intercept the walking corpses. He was disappointed to find a dozen battered Skeletons armed with rusted equipment which probably wouldn't put a dent in a suit of leather armor. The Skeletons were torn apart in less than a minute and not a single man was injured. Someone started telling the classic joke of the "Stumbling Skellie that bit the dust" but never got to the punchline as the final incantation of a Despair Spell caved her mouth in. The Earl tried to scream a warning but it was too late: soldiers and horses were being drained of their lives by some hidden Spellcaster. Von Brakov was one of the very few to survive the spell but he didn't remain standing for long as something heavy landed on his back, pinned him to the ground and tore into his neck. Paralyzed, he slowly fell into unconsciousness amidst wet suction sounds, his mind drifting into a haze of red. He woke up face down, alone, biting the dust -not unlike some Stumbling Skellie- but feeling more alive than he ever had. The night noises and scents spoke directly to him. Now to quench those sudden vicious hunger pangs! The scrawny neck of the harvest accountant formed into his mind. Oh yes, he would pay him and his red ledgers a visit tonight. Red... Red like the sweet coppery blood he would crave for eternity.</Backstory>
